\par \pard\plain \li120 \f4\fs22\b\cf11 Usage \cf0
\par
\par \pard\plain \li120 \f4\fs20  Use the Batch Converter to convert between uncompressed ADFs and
 other, compressed formats. The converter can compress ADFs to ADZ format, decompress ADZs to ADF format,
 decompress DMS' to ADFs and convert DMS' to ADZs. Compression to DMS format is currently not available as
 this format is subject to copyright restrictions.
\par
\par Select disk images for conversion using the \cf9 Add \cf0 button. These will be listed in
 the upper window. Remove single files by selecting the file and clicking the \cf9 Remove \cf0 
 button. The \cf9 Remove All \cf0 button will clear all files from the list.
\par
\par Select the output format using the \cf9 Output Type \cf0 buttons. Selecting the \cf9 Disk
 Image (ADF) \cf0 button will convert listed files to ADF format. Selecting the \cf9 Compressed
 Disk Image (ADZ) \cf0 button will convert listed files to ADZ format. 
\par
\par The button for a format that is unavailable for a particular conversion is disabled i.e.
 The \cf9 Disk Image (ADF) \cf0 button will be disabled if an ADF is selected into the list and
 the \cf9 Compressed Disk Image (ADZ) \cf0 button will be disabled if an ADZ is selected into
 the list. This means that if you select both types, both buttons will be disabled. You should
 select files of only one type or of different types that can be converted to the same output
 type. For example a selection of ADZs and DMS' could all be converted to ADFs.
\par
\par You can reset the \cf9 Output Type \cf0 buttons by closing the Batch Converter and
 reopening it.
\par
\par Start conversion by pressing the \cf9 Start \cf0 button. The converted file's name is removed
 from the list on completion.
\par
\par For each attempted conversion, a status message is printed to the \cf9 Status \cf0
 window reporting success or failure.
\par
\par
\par \pard\plain \li120 \f4\fs22\b\cf11 Temporary Files \cf0
\par
\par \pard\plain \li120 \f4\fs20 When converting between DMS and ADZ formats, ADF Opus creates a
 temporary, intermediate ADF in the \cf9 opustemp \cf0 directory, which is removed after conversion.
 \cf9 opustemp \cf0 is created in the same directory as ADF Opus and is removed when it shuts down.
\par
\par
